April 26, 2018

What is R-Ladies?

  • R-Ladies is a world-wide organization to promote gender diversity in the R community
  • Started in San Francisco in 2012
  • Received funding from the R Consortium in fall 2016 to begin building a global community
  • Currently has 63 chapters and 13,000 members globally

R-Ladies St. Louis

  • Started in September 2017 by Jenine Harris and Chelsea West

  • 4 Meetups: Meet & greet, RCPP Introduction, Introduction to R with DataCamp, Intro Part Deux

  • 9 Instructors: Bobbi Carothers, Shelly Cooper, Alexandra Morshed, Rebecca Willison, Lorinette Worth, Angelique Zeringue, Erin Rossiter, Mary Painter, Christina Garcia

  • 9 Sponsors: NetEffects, Bradford & Galt, WUSTL Brown School Diversity Committee, SLU Center for Outcomes Research, DataCamp, Sage Publishing, R Studio, Locke Data, GitHub

  • More than 125 attendees!
